                  "blocks": {
                    "text_e3Pznx": {
                      "type": "text",
                      "settings": {
                        "text": "<p><strong>1. Check Your Email</strong></p><ul><li>Most stores send a <strong>confirmation email</strong> when your order is placed.</li><li>They often follow up with a <strong>shipping or tracking email</strong> once your order is on its way.</li><li>Look for a <strong>tracking number</strong> or a link to check the order status online.</li></ul><p><strong>2. Log In to Your Account</strong></p><ul><li>If you created an account on the store’s website, log in and go to <strong>“My Orders”</strong> or <strong>“Order History”</strong>.</li><li>You should see the <strong>current status</strong> (e.g., “Processing,” “Shipped,” “Delivered”) and sometimes the <strong>estimated delivery date</strong>.<br/></li></ul><p><strong>3. Use the Tracking Number</strong></p><ul><li>Once your order has shipped, you can usually track it via the <strong>carrier’s website</strong> (like FedEx, UPS, DHL, USPS).</li><li>Enter the tracking number to see <strong>real-time updates</strong> on location and expected delivery.<br/></li></ul><p><strong>4. Contact Customer Service</strong></p><ul><li>If you can’t find information online or via email, reach out to the <strong>store’s customer service</strong>.</li><li>Provide your <strong>order number</strong> and <strong>email</strong> to get updates on your order.</li></ul>",
